.TH "i40e_get_link_status" 9 "i40e_get_link_status" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
i40e_get_link_status \- get status of the HW network link
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "i40e_status" i40e_get_link_status
.BI "(struct i40e_hw *hw "  ","
.BI "bool *link_up "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "hw" 12
pointer to the hw struct
.IP "link_up" 12
pointer to bool (true/false = linkup/linkdown)
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Variable link_up true if link is up, false if link is down.
The variable link_up is invalid if returned value of status != 0

Side effect: LinkStatusEvent reporting becomes enabled
